New Records: Harry Kane scored twice in his 100th game for England
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored his first goal in true Kane style, beating a Finnish defender and unleashing a powerful shot that clipped the underside of the crossbar
Pre-Game Insights: England captain Harry Kane was presented with a golden cap before kickoff and played in gold boots at Wembley Stadium
Post-Match Reflections: Interim England manager Lee Carsley could yet remain in the position for a while longer if the search for Gareth Southgate's permanent successor extends beyond the next international break in October
Miscellaneous Highlights: Nathan Ake went off with an apparent muscle injury shortly before halftime while playing for the Netherlands in a 2-2 draw with Germany
Others: England is playing in the second tier of the Nations League and is level on six points at the top of its group with Greece
